3.2 VULNERABILITY OVERVIEW
3.2.1 вЂ‹OUT-OF-BOUNDS READ CWE-125
вЂ‹The affected applications contain an out-of-bounds read past the end of an allocated structure while parsing specially crafted JT files. This could allow an attacker to execute code in the context of the current process.
вЂ‹CVE-2023-30795 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.8 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).
